social_posts.post_text:
This last month on our trip to Puerto Rico, our group went through the most traumatic events we have ever experienced. It felt like a relentless storm that would never end. The panic attacks , anxiety, sleepless nights, sadness,confusion, chaos felt like it was going to crush our souls. But then, God’s light shone through, as defeated as we felt , his light shone through the darkness and we could start to grasp on to hope again. Through these tragedies our hearts were ripped wide open, faith made stronger and mindsets completely shifted. We are not promised tomorrow. Each moment is so precious . Please do not take it for granted and above all else Love well 🙏🏽❤️ 

.
.
.
.
.

🏝️Looking for a quick getaway to a slower paced island feel? 

🏝️Key Largo is about an hour’s drive from Miami that is filled with activities for the whole family!

🏝️John Pennekamp Coral Reef State Park is the country’s first undersea park created to protect the only living coral reef in the Continental United States . It spans over 70 nautical square miles! 
They offer snorkeling, diving, and glass bottom boat tours to explore the reef and there is even an underwater 4,000 lb. “Christ of the Deep” bronze statue! 

🏝️Lastly is Harry Harris Beach ( technically located in Tavernier/ just a 10 min drive from Key Largo)
A beautiful calm beach with plenty of shade and places to bbq. 
🔑 Tip: Weekdays are FREE and weekends (always free for county residents) they charge an admission fee.

The Key Biscayne Lighthouse is a historic landmark located on the southern tip of Key Biscayne, a small island off the coast of Miami, Florida. Built in 1825, the lighthouse has stood the test of time, guiding ships safely through the treacherous waters of the Florida Straits for almost two centuries. The Key Biscayne Lighthouse is a symbol of strength, resilience, and hope for sailors and visitors alike.

.

Top Beaches in Key Biscayne 🏝️ 

1.	Crandon Park Beach - This is a popular beach with crystal clear water and white sand.

2.	Mashta Flats Beach - This beach is a hidden gem that is often overlooked by tourists. It has a secluded location and calm waters, making it a great spot for swimming and sunbathing.

3.	Hobie Beach - This beach is also known as Windsurfer Beach, as it is a popular spot for windsurfing and kiteboarding. It has soft sand, clear water, and views of the Miami skyline.

📍Tarpon Springs 🇬🇷

Tarpon Springs is a charming city located on the Gulf Coast of Florida. 
It has a rich Greek heritage that dates back to the early 1900’s when Greeks immigrants settled in that area. Tarpon Springs became infamous for its sponge diving industry, which originated with the Greek divers who introduced the technique to the region. 
The sponge diving industry is still thriving and an integral part of the city’s identity and economy.
